1
00:01:42,480 --> 00:01:44,760
Run for Young

2
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:56,240
Big Mouth!

3
00:01:56,600 --> 00:01:57,640
The Chinese New Year is coming.

4
00:01:57,800 --> 00:01:59,080
All families reunite.

5
00:01:59,160 --> 00:01:59,920
Yeah.

6
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:02,760
Your dad may come back.

7
00:02:03,800 --> 00:02:04,720
He's a grown-up.

8
00:02:04,960 --> 00:02:06,000
If he wants to come home,

9
00:02:06,360 --> 00:02:07,600
he will find his own way.

10
00:02:07,960 --> 00:02:09,000
It has been so many years.

11
00:02:09,200 --> 00:02:10,360
You never tried to look for him either, huh?

12
00:02:11,320 --> 00:02:11,980
Look...

13
00:02:13,040 --> 00:02:14,080
Looking for what?

14
00:02:17,200 --> 00:02:17,840
Hey.

15
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:19,640
What the hell is he doing elsewhere?

16
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:21,120
How could I know?

17
00:02:23,880 --> 00:02:24,880
Do you miss him?

18
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:28,960
Or

19
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:30,040
I can share my fatherly love

20
00:02:30,600 --> 00:02:31,280
with you.

21
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:33,280
Good idea.

22
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:34,320
Then do you want half of

23
00:02:34,480 --> 00:02:35,200
the maternal love I have?

24
00:02:35,820 --> 00:02:36,460
That's OK.

25
00:02:36,640 --> 00:02:38,160
I think I have got enough care from my mother.

26
00:02:38,480 --> 00:02:39,160
OK.

27
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:45,440
The Spring Festival is coming soon.

28
00:02:46,760 --> 00:02:47,380
Right.

29
00:02:49,080 --> 00:02:50,040
Today is the Little New Year.

30
00:02:51,080 --> 00:02:52,040
An Aunt

31
00:02:52,440 --> 00:02:53,800
will have dinner with us in the evening.

32
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:55,840
Which aunt?

33
00:02:55,880 --> 00:02:57,200
None of your business.

34
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:58,840
Then why did you tell me that?

35
00:02:58,960 --> 00:03:00,320
I am asking you to come home early for dinner.

36
00:03:09,160 --> 00:03:13,000
Episode 8 Set off Firecrackers for the New Year

37
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:23,400
- Stop fighting. - Alright.

38
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:24,160
No, no.

39
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:25,120
No, no.

40
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:30,440
Alright.

41
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:31,360
Stop it.

42
00:03:32,080 --> 00:03:32,760
Two sausages.

43
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:33,520
Sausage.

44
00:03:35,600 --> 00:03:37,320
Hang one bacon here.

45
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:39,800
Come on.

46
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:40,960
OK.

47
00:03:41,040 --> 00:03:41,800
We are here.

48
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:43,800
Aunt!

49
00:03:44,440 --> 00:03:45,720
My dad asked me to bring it to you.

50
00:03:47,320 --> 00:03:48,200
Thanks.

51
00:03:48,480 --> 00:03:49,920
Please send my thanks to your father.

52
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:51,680
You can go and thank him yourself.

53
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:55,720
Did your father tell you about that?

54
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:57,760
What?

55
00:04:00,320 --> 00:04:01,640
Never mind.

56
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:03,040
Your father is so nice.

57
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:04,240
You're welcome. I'm leaving.

58
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:04,920
OK.

59
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:05,920
-Bye, Aunt. - Bye, Aunt.

60
00:04:05,920 --> 00:04:06,520
Bye-bye.

61
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:10,720
Why is there still a piece of bacon left?

62
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:15,080
Hey, the Chinese New Year is coming.

63
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:17,640
Do you want to give it to Anran?

64
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:20,280
Bacon is not the gift among classmates.

65
00:04:20,280 --> 00:04:21,600
What if it is popular this year?

66
00:04:21,640 --> 00:04:23,880
Do you think bacon is the popular gift among classmates?

67
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:25,480
- No, it isn't. - Old-fashioned.

68
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:27,360
Then you told me to send pork liver as a gift last time.

69
00:04:27,760 --> 00:04:30,040
Pig liver is such a popular gift.

70
00:04:30,080 --> 00:04:30,680
Extremely popular.

71
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:31,280
Right, pork liver is so popular.

72
00:04:31,280 --> 00:04:32,360
Bacon is so old-fashioned.

73
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:33,240
Sure.

74
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:34,840
You shouldn't send bacon to anyone.

75
00:04:34,840 --> 00:04:35,720
Forget it.

76
00:04:36,880 --> 00:04:37,560
Is it because

77
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:38,920
that you haven't seen her for many days in winter vacation.

78
00:04:38,920 --> 00:04:40,240
Certainly not.

79
00:04:41,480 --> 00:04:42,200
I

80
00:04:42,240 --> 00:04:43,760
think...

81
00:04:43,760 --> 00:04:44,400
What?

82
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:47,360
I want to check if she gets over with that?

83
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:48,880
Then you should go and see her.

84
00:04:48,880 --> 00:04:49,680
I won't go.

85
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:50,800
OK, we will go with you.

86
00:04:51,240 --> 00:04:52,160
Together.

87
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:52,860
We can go together.

88
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:54,320
I

89
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:55,640
think

90
00:04:55,640 --> 00:04:57,040
going to see her alone is weird.

91
00:04:57,560 --> 00:05:00,960
We know that.

92
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:02,600
Let's go.

93
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:04,520
If you didn't mention it...

94
00:05:04,640 --> 00:05:05,280
We are here.

95
00:05:05,780 --> 00:05:06,400
I won't go.

96
00:05:06,440 --> 00:05:07,360
But you do care about her.

97
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:08,280
Go, you go.

98
00:05:08,880 --> 00:05:09,720
Hurry up.

99
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:11,240
Almost there.

100
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:13,880
A blessing character is posted here.

101
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:16,200
I shouldn't do that.

102
00:05:16,360 --> 00:05:17,360
What's wrong with it?

103
00:05:17,640 --> 00:05:18,720
Come on.

104
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:19,440
Ring the doorbell.

105
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:22,960
Such a big blessing character.

106
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:26,320
Hello, Uncle.

107
00:05:26,320 --> 00:05:26,940
There you are.

108
00:05:27,280 --> 00:05:28,360
The Chinese New Year is coming.

109
00:05:28,360 --> 00:05:29,920
He brings some bacon to Anran.

110
00:05:30,720 --> 00:05:31,600
Thank you.

111
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:33,000
You are so nice.

112
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:35,240
- Okay, I'm going to tell Anran. - Okay.

113
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:36,360
Anran.

114
00:05:36,440 --> 00:05:37,600
Your classmates are here.

115
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:41,240
Anran.

116
00:05:41,240 --> 00:05:42,080
He's looking for you.

117
00:05:42,080 --> 00:05:43,280
Doggo brings you bacon.

118
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:50,340
Anran.

119
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:52,440
This is my home phone number.

120
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:56,040
I will give it to him.

121
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:58,640
I didn't say anything about him.

122
00:05:59,680 --> 00:06:01,240
But it seems that he wants to see you.

123
00:06:02,360 --> 00:06:03,840
Jiao!

124
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:05,800
So you're looking for Ma Tian.

125
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:06,600
Ma Tian.

126
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:07,400
Looking for Ma Tian.

127
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:09,280
Don't talk nonsense.

128
00:06:11,240 --> 00:06:11,920
Doggo.

129
00:06:11,920 --> 00:06:13,560
Will you set off fireworks during the Spring Festival?

130
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:15,320
Sure!

131
00:06:15,320 --> 00:06:16,240
We will go to the riverside to set off fireworks.

132
00:06:16,400 --> 00:06:17,400
Take me with you.

133
00:06:17,960 --> 00:06:18,880
You like fireworks?

134
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:20,160
That's what we do during this special festival.

135
00:06:22,560 --> 00:06:23,720
- Good. - It's a deal.

136
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:25,040
It's a deal.

137
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:26,080
Then I'm leaving.

138
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:27,400
Take care, you guys.

139
00:06:27,760 --> 00:06:28,880
Bye.

140
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:29,760
Bye.

141
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:35,440
You are the son of Mr. Ma, right?

142
00:06:35,480 --> 00:06:36,920
So handsome.

143
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:38,360
Dad, someone is looking for you.

144
00:06:39,160 --> 00:06:40,600
Sir, I come to pay a Happy New Year call.

145
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:44,840
Dehua, why you are here at the night of Little New Year?

146
00:06:45,120 --> 00:06:46,240
Today is the special occasion before the Chinese New Year.

147
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:48,040
I come to pay a Happy New Year call.

148
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:49,880
Go back.

149
00:06:49,880 --> 00:06:51,160
Go home and stay with your family.

150
00:06:51,560 --> 00:06:54,440
It's my hard time and I don't have any interest
in the Chinese New Year.

151
00:06:54,960 --> 00:06:57,880
I have a project that hasn't been approved yet.

152
00:06:59,680 --> 00:07:00,320
Dehua.

153
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:01,920
If your project

154
00:07:02,120 --> 00:07:03,640
conform to all the standards and specifications,

155
00:07:04,520 --> 00:07:05,760
why can't it be approved?

156
00:07:05,760 --> 00:07:07,120
You're right.

157
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:08,680
But I am in a hurry.

158
00:07:10,320 --> 00:07:12,600
As long as you are willing to help me, Sir,

159
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:14,600
we will definitely make it worth your while.

160
00:07:15,440 --> 00:07:16,480
All right, just go.

161
00:07:16,920 --> 00:07:18,440
Go home, come on.

162
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:23,920
Goodbye, Uncle.

163
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:30,440
This is Zhu Weijiao's phone number.

164
00:07:31,880 --> 00:07:33,120
Be sure to call her.

165
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:37,880
I want to tell you

166
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:40,080
I'm not going abroad.

167
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:41,720
I know.

168
00:07:42,040 --> 00:07:43,320
You stay because of her.

169
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:45,760
I have many reasons to stay.

170
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:47,000
And it's mainly because

171
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,800
the countless delicacies in Chongqing.

172
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,400
How do you explain it to your family?

173
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:54,840
We'll talk about it then.

174
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:55,680
What can I do?

175
00:07:57,200 --> 00:07:58,280
I envy you so much

176
00:07:58,720 --> 00:08:00,320
for having such a firm reason.

177
00:08:01,320 --> 00:08:02,200
Are you sure?

178
00:08:02,840 --> 00:08:03,680
Sure about what?

179
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:05,200
Study abroad.

180
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:06,680
Yes.

181
00:08:06,960 --> 00:08:07,680
Or what?

182
00:08:08,920 --> 00:08:10,200
But after you going abroad,

183
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:11,640
what about Doggo?

184
00:08:12,480 --> 00:08:13,080
Doggo.

185
00:08:14,080 --> 00:08:15,320
You're so smart.

186
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:16,880
I bet you know his feeling about you.

187
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:18,800
If I pretend that I didn't know his feelings,

188
00:08:19,120 --> 00:08:21,040
nobody would believe me.

189
00:08:22,720 --> 00:08:23,340
Yeah.

190
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:24,600
Well.

191
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:27,280
For a boy of his age,

192
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:28,880
it's difficult for him

193
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:30,320
to not cause

194
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:31,840
any troubles or pressures

195
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:33,480
to the one

196
00:08:33,760 --> 00:08:35,040
he adores.

197
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:38,480
It's just because he has been so nice to me.

198
00:08:39,160 --> 00:08:40,000
Sometimes,

199
00:08:40,160 --> 00:08:41,920
I don't know what to do with him.

200
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:44,480
What should I do?

201
00:08:44,680 --> 00:08:45,760
Have some liquor?

202
00:08:45,839 --> 00:08:46,440
Okay.

203
00:08:46,440 --> 00:08:47,079
A little.

204
00:08:48,199 --> 00:08:48,839
Enough.

205
00:08:48,839 --> 00:08:49,520
Good.

206
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:56,160
Have some food.

207
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:56,880
You too.

208
00:09:05,280 --> 00:09:06,360
Son of a gun.

209
00:09:06,360 --> 00:09:07,680
Where are your manners?

210
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:14,320
Forget it.

211
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:16,080
Today is a special festival.

212
00:09:16,520 --> 00:09:17,680
Don't blame him.

213
00:09:18,160 --> 00:09:19,240
Let's enjoy our meals.

214
00:09:19,240 --> 00:09:20,960
I can't.

215
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:22,240
Then don't eat anything if you don't want to.

216
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:25,720
OK. I won't.

217
00:09:27,440 --> 00:09:28,680
Stop!

218
00:09:30,760 --> 00:09:32,520
She is your Aunt Zhang. You should accept her.

219
00:09:36,440 --> 00:09:37,520
Why should I accept her?

220
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:40,200
It is none of my business.

221
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:42,760
I only have one mom.

222
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:45,240
Forget it.

223
00:09:46,720 --> 00:09:47,520
Forget it.

224
00:09:50,040 --> 00:09:51,480
Let's eat. Just leave him alone.

225
00:09:51,560 --> 00:09:52,520
Sit.

226
00:09:56,760 --> 00:09:58,040
That son of a gun.

227
00:09:58,560 --> 00:10:00,880
He once broke someone's window during the festival.

228
00:10:01,280 --> 00:10:03,120
I paid a lot of money for him.

229
00:10:03,680 --> 00:10:05,840
Why is he pulling the long face?

230
00:10:06,760 --> 00:10:08,200
He only misses his mother.

231
00:10:08,680 --> 00:10:10,440
But his mother won't come to fix any problems for him.

232
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:13,760
He is grown up now.

233
00:10:14,160 --> 00:10:15,600
He has his own ideas.

234
00:10:17,160 --> 00:10:19,280
Well, he needs some time.

235
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:44,880
Jiaojiao, come down for dinner.

236
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:47,280
I'm not hungry.

237
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:48,560
Eat no matter what.

238
00:10:48,560 --> 00:10:49,800
It's late!

239
00:10:50,560 --> 00:10:51,720
Wait a minute.

240
00:11:02,680 --> 00:11:03,880
Mom.

241
00:11:03,880 --> 00:11:05,560
Uncle wants to talk to you.

242
00:11:14,720 --> 00:11:15,320
Hello.

243
00:11:17,560 --> 00:11:19,240
Jiaojiao, it's for you.

244
00:11:24,160 --> 00:11:24,960
Zhu Weijiao.

245
00:11:29,440 --> 00:11:30,600
What's wrong, Ma Tian?

246
00:11:32,640 --> 00:11:34,640
School starts in a few days.

247
00:11:35,160 --> 00:11:36,200
Zhu Weijiao.

248
00:11:36,360 --> 00:11:37,480
Yes, Ma Tian.

249
00:11:38,120 --> 00:11:39,480
I am alone at home.

250
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:41,720
I can't cook.

251
00:11:42,280 --> 00:11:43,800
I want to have dinner with someone.

252
00:11:44,680 --> 00:11:45,800
But I can't find Anran.

253
00:11:48,160 --> 00:11:49,840
Then why are you telling me?

254
00:11:51,040 --> 00:11:52,200
Would you like to

255
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:54,480
have dinner with me?

256
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:02,160
All right.

257
00:12:02,720 --> 00:12:04,480
No one cooks for me at home, too.

258
00:12:06,640 --> 00:12:07,360
Then

259
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:08,840
I'll see you in half an hour.

260
00:12:09,640 --> 00:12:10,240
OK.

261
00:12:17,800 --> 00:12:18,760
Jiaojiao.

262
00:12:19,480 --> 00:12:22,040
Don't tell everyone that no one cooks for you at home.

263
00:12:22,640 --> 00:12:24,640
People might think you were an orphan.

264
00:12:24,920 --> 00:12:26,320
They may alienate you then.

265
00:12:26,880 --> 00:12:29,400
Why are you eavesdropping on my phone?

266
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:30,800
It's annoying.

267
00:12:31,780 --> 00:12:32,400
Jiao.

268
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:34,000
Where are you going, Jiao?

269
00:12:34,280 --> 00:12:35,200
Go away.

270
00:12:35,440 --> 00:12:36,760
I don't have time to play with you.

271
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:37,320
What are you doing?

272
00:12:37,440 --> 00:12:38,040
I am not in the mood today.

273
00:12:38,120 --> 00:12:39,160
You are wearing a dress.

274
00:12:42,280 --> 00:12:43,240
So happy she is!

275
00:12:47,520 --> 00:12:48,840
How's business, Aunt?

276
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:50,280
Doggo, Big Mouth!

277
00:12:52,520 --> 00:12:53,480
Anran.

278
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:54,160
Anran.

279
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:55,360
Why are you here?

280
00:12:55,800 --> 00:12:57,800
Dad asked me to bring you something for the Spring Festival.

281
00:13:02,080 --> 00:13:03,040
So nice.

282
00:13:03,040 --> 00:13:05,200
Of course, courtesy calls for reciprocity.

283
00:13:08,760 --> 00:13:09,560
Doggo.

284
00:13:09,640 --> 00:13:10,480
How about going out to play?

285
00:13:10,920 --> 00:13:11,760
Well, let's go.

286
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:14,400
What do you care?

287
00:13:15,160 --> 00:13:16,200
Well...

288
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:16,800
You go.

289
00:13:17,520 --> 00:13:18,440
- You go ahead to play. - Then let's go.

290
00:14:12,080 --> 00:14:13,520
Why are you dressed up?

291
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:15,080
You're not dressed down!

292
00:14:17,120 --> 00:14:18,200
What do you want to eat?

293
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:19,160
Chuanchuan!

294
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:24,880
We shouldn't eat Chuanchuan by the roadside.

295
00:14:25,160 --> 00:14:27,280
It is not hygienic.

296
00:14:27,960 --> 00:14:29,920
How about western food?

297
00:14:33,640 --> 00:14:34,440
Sir.

298
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:35,400
Sit closer.

299
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:40,840
Sit closer to me!

300
00:14:40,840 --> 00:14:41,800
Why are you sitting so far?

301
00:14:41,800 --> 00:14:43,440
Don't block the passage!

302
00:14:44,520 --> 00:14:45,560
Sit here.

303
00:14:56,720 --> 00:14:57,720
Cook like this.

304
00:15:04,560 --> 00:15:05,120
Sir.

305
00:15:05,120 --> 00:15:06,160
Excuse me, how do you want your beef

306
00:15:06,160 --> 00:15:07,520
to be cooked?

307
00:15:07,560 --> 00:15:09,000
Of course, well-done.

308
00:15:09,240 --> 00:15:10,360
Otherwise, it may cause diarrhea.

309
00:15:22,840 --> 00:15:24,120
You can't eat spicy food?

310
00:15:24,840 --> 00:15:25,560
A little.

311
00:15:26,280 --> 00:15:27,120
No way.

312
00:15:28,480 --> 00:15:29,360
Let's play games.

313
00:15:29,400 --> 00:15:30,440
Those who lose must eat spicy food.

314
00:15:31,320 --> 00:15:31,920
Follow me.

315
00:15:33,220 --> 00:15:33,820
Make a fist.

316
00:15:35,280 --> 00:15:37,480
Fifty, twenty, and five.

317
00:15:38,600 --> 00:15:39,960
You can choose this one or the other.

318
00:15:40,840 --> 00:15:41,440
Again!

319
00:15:41,960 --> 00:15:43,520
Fifteen, twenty, twenty.

320
00:15:44,160 --> 00:15:45,680
You have to shout it out.

321
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:47,600
Yell out and come again.

322
00:15:48,760 --> 00:15:50,440
Fifteen, twenty.

323
00:15:50,440 --> 00:15:51,280
Twenty.

324
00:16:12,920 --> 00:16:13,640
Grandpa Ding.

325
00:16:14,160 --> 00:16:14,760
How are you?

326
00:16:15,760 --> 00:16:16,680
- Help yourself. - OK.

327
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:23,240
Grandpa Ding.

328
00:16:23,400 --> 00:16:24,160
What's wrong?

329
00:16:29,680 --> 00:16:30,280
Madam.

330
00:16:30,640 --> 00:16:32,400
You don't need to do this on your own.

331
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:33,960
Just ask your grandson to do this for you.

332
00:16:34,040 --> 00:16:35,240
Running up and down

333
00:16:35,240 --> 00:16:36,160
is not good for your health.

334
00:16:37,760 --> 00:16:38,520
Here, here you are.

335
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:39,960
Listen to me.

336
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:41,640
Take good care of your grandma and grandpa.

337
00:16:41,640 --> 00:16:42,880
They are not young anymore.

338
00:16:43,680 --> 00:16:44,840
Don't underestimate any healthy problems.

339
00:16:45,320 --> 00:16:46,840
Do not be careless or make any mistakes.

340
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:48,680
Understand?

341
00:16:49,480 --> 00:16:50,200
Understood!

342
00:16:52,840 --> 00:16:53,480
Is this ready?

343
00:16:53,480 --> 00:16:54,120
Yeah.

344
00:16:56,680 --> 00:16:57,800
Have a try, tasty?

345
00:16:57,800 --> 00:16:58,760
I have not eaten.

346
00:17:02,240 --> 00:17:02,880
Delicious.

347
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:04,160
Isn't it?

348
00:17:05,720 --> 00:17:07,080
I don't want to go home so soon.

349
00:17:07,880 --> 00:17:09,040
I didn't push you.

350
00:17:09,560 --> 00:17:10,200
Thank you, Doggo.

351
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:12,040
Why are you so polite?

352
00:17:12,560 --> 00:17:13,200
Right.

353
00:17:14,560 --> 00:17:15,399
After all, we are now

354
00:17:15,399 --> 00:17:16,639
very good friends.

355
00:17:19,879 --> 00:17:20,560
Really?

356
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:22,080
Yes, of course.

357
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:28,760
Oh, drag.

358
00:17:29,680 --> 00:17:30,720
I'll get some sesame oil.

359
00:17:36,760 --> 00:17:39,399
LOVE IN A LIFETIME

360
00:18:30,280 --> 00:18:31,080
Are you OK?

361
00:18:36,640 --> 00:18:38,040
What else would you like to eat?

362
00:18:38,280 --> 00:18:39,160
I'll order it for you.

363
00:18:41,520 --> 00:18:42,320
Doggo?

364
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:45,240
We'll have hot pot next time.

365
00:18:45,240 --> 00:18:46,480
Eat something slightly spicy.

366
00:18:46,640 --> 00:18:48,040
This is really too spicy.

367
00:18:49,720 --> 00:18:51,760
I thought I was used to spicy food.

368
00:18:52,800 --> 00:18:54,240
It turns out that I haven't.

369
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:56,800
I can't even pretend to be used to that flavor.

370
00:18:58,360 --> 00:18:59,680
It makes me cry.

371
00:19:00,400 --> 00:19:01,960
I'm such a loser.

372
00:19:02,680 --> 00:19:04,560
Eating a hot pot makes me cry.

373
00:19:05,680 --> 00:19:06,920
Doggo, I'm sorry.

374
00:19:19,560 --> 00:19:20,160
It's the Chinese New year.

375
00:19:20,160 --> 00:19:21,400
Can you stop talking about this?

376
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:22,880
Thank you and sorry?

377
00:19:22,880 --> 00:19:23,840
What do you want?

378
00:20:01,720 --> 00:20:03,560
I still can't forget him.

379
00:20:18,560 --> 00:20:19,720
Oh.

380
00:20:19,720 --> 00:20:21,760
On Chinese New Year's Eve,
we will have a dinner with other families.

381
00:20:23,120 --> 00:20:24,040
It will be late.

382
00:20:24,800 --> 00:20:26,000
I won't go setting off firecrackers.

383
00:21:35,360 --> 00:21:36,560
I'm scared about that.

384
00:21:37,240 --> 00:21:41,920
I'm so scared that my father can't survive, Doggo.

385
00:21:42,960 --> 00:21:44,000
Doggo.

386
00:21:47,520 --> 00:21:48,320
Doggo.

387
00:21:52,800 --> 00:21:54,120
Why are you crying?

388
00:21:58,960 --> 00:22:00,240
I don't know.

389
00:22:00,280 --> 00:22:01,280
Watching you cry

390
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:04,240
